Description:

The Literature Survey phase involves studying existing agricultural recommendation systems, crop prediction techniques, and machine learning-based smart farming solutions. Various research papers, journals, case studies, online resources, and agricultural technology platforms are reviewed to understand how artificial intelligence and data analytics are applied in modern agriculture.
The survey focuses on different machine learning algorithms such as Decision Tree, Random Forest, K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN), Logistic Regression, Neural Networks, and K-Means Clustering for crop recommendation and agricultural prediction. These algorithms are compared based on their accuracy, efficiency, advantages, and limitations to identify the most suitable approach for the OptiCrop system.
The study also includes data preprocessing methods, feature engineering techniques, dataset balancing, and evaluation metrics used in crop prediction models. Existing smart farming systems and precision agriculture technologies are analyzed to identify current challenges and areas for improvement.
This phase helps in understanding the latest advancements in agricultural technology, selecting appropriate machine learning techniques, and designing an efficient crop recommendation system. The knowledge gained from the literature survey serves as the foundation for data analysis, model development, system implementation, and future enhancements of the OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization System.
